Well in that case you need to use `angular` or `react` to do that easily. You can do it with `jQuery` as well. In that case you need to do that by replacing `html` in your content area. Here is your rendering section

    &lt;div id=&quot;MainContent&quot;&gt;
        @RenderBody()
    &lt;/div&gt;
Take an extra `div` there where you want to switch viewes.

    &lt;div id=&quot;MainContent&quot;&gt;
        @RenderBody()
        &lt;div id=&quot;contentView&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

Now what you need to is, create `ajax` request to your controller and return partial views and replace that view in that particular area in `contentView`. Here is an action for a partial view

    [HttpGet]
    public ActionResult PartialViewUser(){
        return Partial(&quot;_UserPartial&quot;);
    }
Create an ajax request to that `action`

    $.ajax({
        type: &#39;GET&#39;,
        url: &#39;/Controller/PartialViewUser&#39;,
        success: function(resp){
            // Clear html from contentView ID
            // Then append new response
            $(&quot;#contentView&quot;).empty().append(resp);
        },
        error: function(resp){
            console.log(resp);
        }
    });

You are good to go. This will switch viewes for you inside `contentView` div. Remember, you need only return partial view to achieve that.

